records.addlTxt:
Defendant James Willie Brown in court with attorney Louis E Epps.  Paul L Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction; credit for 2 days time served.

If revoked and employed at the time of revocation, defendant can have release for work. If unemployed when revoked, defendant can participate in HOC work programs. 

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 12 MONTHS with the following conditions:

1) AODA assessment and comply with any treatment;
2) Successfully complete an anger management or a Batterers Intervention program;
3) No violent contact with the victim;
4) Follow any family court orders that arise out of pending case;
5) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
6) Court WAIVED DNA surcharge because the Court finds the defendant is not likely to reoffend;

Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
